<br>
  It should be interesting though the extent to which they give lower levels a 'fair' chance in pvp.  The ten level suggested by Velox sounds reasonable, therefore it is nearly ruled out on that basis.  On TZ, 8 levels (with resist gear appropriate for level) difference with equally skilled opponents was enough for the higher level to win 9 out of 10 times.  With an inceasing difference in either skill or gear (in the lower level players' favor) success rate for the higher level dropped fairly evenly.  With this change, I'm guessing the drop will be about the same with the only difference being that a fairly inept higher level player can now be dispatched by even a moderately skilled/equipped lower level player.  <br>
<br>
<br>
